author: Rob Braxman Tech
description:
This video is a primer on the use of Voice Over IP (VOIP) in a personal setting to achieve privacy goals. Normally VOIP is a well known tool for use as a landline and also extensively for business use. But there is little understanding of how this can be used for privacy or on a mobile phone.

This video will also introduce the Brax Virtual Phone Service which is a specific privacy implementation of VOIP.
